Text.Value: It's true... it's still there. I heard the only one to walk out alive from that place was the Bhaalspawn who killed Sarevok all those years ago.
For your sake as much as any other, I hope you found the mastermind behind him...
Perhaps you're right. Well, in any case - thank you.
'Candulhallow's Tombstones' - any idea where that is?
Sarevok was but a withered husk. There's worse than him out there.
Then it's over... at least, until a new Bhaalspawn emerges.
Hells, no witness has even claimed to have seen it in decades.
A shrivelled undead? Eugh. Thank you for putting him down. Would think the Bhaalists want the dead to stay that way.
But you killed Sarevok again. You can survive. You can end this. I know it.
Kill her.
He dragged me to a mystic blood-pool. I drowned in the death-fluid.
Oh. Ah. Thank you. I didn't do much, though.
The things you must have seen to find that out. Tell me you put a stop to it.
The tribunal is not the heart of the cult... but the Temple of Bhaal itself.
Have you won your freedom yet?
I have to kill you. I will honour my duty as an Unholy Assassin.
'Candulhallow's Tombstones' - any idea where that is?
Fascinating... I wish I could put half as much into my final report, but, well, I think my superiors would rather I just stick to the facts.
I'm no hero. Bhaal's hand forced me to kill my partner.
Any more to report on the Bhaalist resurgence?
You are looking at Bhaal's newest Unholy Assassin.
Your hope spurred me on.
You don't need to worry about the tribunal or the Bhaalist resurgence anymore. I killed Orin. She was the one behind it all.
He never left... He's been rotting beneath the city all this time.
There's a place called 'Candulhallow's Tombstones' that I've seen cropping up in the reports. Seems to be where the murderers are sent once they've completed their kills.
I have a gut feeling Bhaal made me. I don't have a mother.
I knew it had to be someone other than Sarevok!
There is much I didn't tell you. I am Bhaal's child. I killed my own sister.
I killed Sarevok at the tribunal.
Understandable. It must have been quite the ordeal.
Tell me everything.
I'm still working on it.
I killed their leader - my own sister.
Ah, then I'll leave you to it. I'll stretch out my stint here as long as my break allows, in case you find anything.
First I slaughtered Orin, then I took my rightful place as Bhaal's new Chosen.
So history repeated itself...
The tribunal is not the heart of the cult... but the Temple of Bhaal itself.
The Baldurians need not worry about any more murders.
Damn right. I turned down the power of a god to save you all.
So she was the one who was staging those dioramas of murder?
I found the tribunal and killed Sarevok and his granddaughter Orin.
The cult is gone, for now.
Ah - I was hoping I hadn't missed you. The patriars are safe, but it took longer to calm them down than I was hoping.
You must have seen some troubling things to find that out. Do you know who your own mother is?
It's a total mystery.
I suppose even Bhaal must have needed new blood at some point.
It's too disgusting. I don't want to think about it.
I found the tribunal and killed Sarevok.

EditorData.logicalname: DEVELLA KNEW I KILLED ORIN ALREADY

Text.Value: *This woman sees a fairy tale hero in the making. But you are the grinning villain. You always will be.*
You - WHAT?! No... NO...
Nonetheless, thank you.
Can you remind me where I was supposed to go?
Fascinating... I mean, ahem, how horrible. Well done for making it out.
You should think about joining the Fist, you know. We could do with more people like you.
There's a lot more to it... I have to find the Temple of Bhaal now.
He had a granddaughter?! What are you saying, Devella, of course he did. If there's one thing you can rely on a Bhaalspawn to do, it's to spread their Lord's seed. Vigorously.
I found the tribunal and killed Sarevok.
This is excellent news.
That cult is disgusting. Did you know that Sarevok had a child with his own daughter?
I see it in your eyes... He got you, didn't he? I'm sorry...
It's all over... I faced Bhaal himself.
Describe in violent detail how you put an end to the Bhaalist resurgence.
You - joined them?! Shit.
Oh, that's... oh...
There was a lot of blood. Best I spare you the details.
Tell me, how did your investigations into the Bhaalist tribunal go?
If that is true, you must be of unparalleled value to your Father.
End her.
That's... awful. I'm not sure if I'm glad or disgusted that you handled that instead of me. But you did handle it.
A Bhaalist servant tells me I'm a pureblood Spawn - but I don't know what it means.
Bhaal is not a living man any longer... I can't even begin to fathom how you were born. Let's not dwell.
I really don't have time for that. Just be thankful it's over.
What I'd give to see the place... There must be so much history completely untouched...
Can you remind me where I was supposed to go?
I just did what needed to be done.
I don't feel like talking about it.
Thanks, but I just want to live a normal life now.
There was a monster - the Slayer - words cannot describe it.
Of course, of course... I am. Believe me, I really am.
You're a wonder. Soon you will be sewn into the very fabric of this city as one of our legends. It's an honour to know you.
Don't look up to me. Bhaal made me cause the death of a whole village once.
Father Bhaal will never forget Baldur's Gate.
Know the Baldurians will accept you as a hero. We did as much with the spawn who first killed Sarevok. You are our champion, now, too.
I'm no hero. Bhaal's hand forced me to kill my best friend.
It sounds as if his cult has crumbled, even if it took everything you had to stop it?
It was easier than I expected, actually.
It wouldn't be the Gate if our favourite superstition was entirely thwarted. But you've stopped him for now, at least.
Not many would have it in them to do as you have.
I didn't live. Bhaal killed me. But I was resurrected, free of his curse.
Devastate her.
I'd say you should join the Fist - we need detectives like you. But I suspect you'll need a good long rest.
Leave.
I won't go into quite as much detail in my report, but thank you nonetheless. It's nice to have the full picture.
OH! You magnificent bastard. You faced him and LIVED! You have to tell me how!
So he was back. I was right!
No matter what you are - what you were - you are the best of the Baldurians now.
Hope you're closer to some answers, Bhaalspawn. Did you find the tribunal?
It's not a place I'd ever heard of, if I'm honest. But rumour has it there were some hidden cellars somewhere near the Elfsong. If I had to look anywhere, I'd look there.
A duel between Bhaalspawn, in the Temple of Bhaal itself! What I would have given to be a witness to that.
That cult is disgusting. Did you know that Sarevok had a child with his own daughter?

Synopsis: If Devella survives the Serial Killer, she will be at Basilisk Gate with this one liner
